main event: Observers reported seeing 3 unidentified flying objects in the sky over Colorado Springs from 2232 to 2250 on July 19, 1952.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 18 minutes,Objects appeared to be moving and maneuvering in the sky at high altitude,The objects were described as white or bright in color,There was no physical evidence or photographs captured in the report,Observers could not identify the objects despite their prolonged observation.
